RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 1 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 75. Maiden Claiming Purse 29000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $50,000.

CLAIM.OWNER: Haagsma David Haagsma John R and Vanderdussen Robert John

RACE.FOOTNOTES: HOUSE OF MAGIC took control early, led two wide around the bend, three wide into the lane, drifted a bit in upper stretch, remained unchallenged into the final furlong and stayed clear under a drive. PAID IN GOLD stalked the pacesetter from outside, went three wide around the turn, chased after the winner into the final furlong, could not summon the needed late kick but held the place. AVA'S STORM bobbled leaving the gate, stalked from inside into and around the bend, drew closer nearing the midstretch but finished evenly late while missing the place. ACCELERINA chased off the rail early, went three wide around the turn, four wide into the lane, had to alter out a bit from behind PAID IN GOLD in upper stretch and lacked a rally in the late stages.

ENTRY.NAME: Ava's Storm
ENTRY.COMMENT: bobbled, stalked inside, missed 2nd

ENTRY.NAME: Accelerina
ENTRY.COMMENT: chased off rail, 3-4wide, altered bit upper, no rally

ENTRY.NAME: House of Magic
ENTRY.COMMENT: pace 2-3wide, drifted bit upper, stayed clear

ENTRY.NAME: Paid in Gold
ENTRY.COMMENT: stalked outside, 3wide, held 2nd

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 2 6F Dirt CR: 98. Starter Allowance Purse 22000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $16,000 OR LESS. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since April 20 Allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SUNRISE JOURNEY established the front quickly then eased over to the inside on the backstretch, showed the way along the inside through the turn, moved off the fence in upper stretch, steered out past the eighth pole and held well. KANT BEAT THE ROCK stalked off the rail then between rivals in the two path around the bend, finished willingly late and edged rival for the place honors. ESTABLISHED brushed the gate to break out slightly, chased outside a rival then three deep around the bend, finished evenly in the final furlong behind the leader and got edged for the place. BIG SWEDE broke a bit slow, tracked off the rail to the turn, went three to four wide into the lane, moved out in upper stretch and kept on to close the gap and earn a minor award. MAJESTIC WIND chased up close from inside early, took hold when the leader was crossing over at the half-mile pole, chased along the rail through the turn inside a pair of rivals and tired in the final furlong. PER RULING FROM HIWU, KANT BEAT THE ROCK WAS DISQUALIFIED FOR POSITIVE TEST.

ENTRY.NAME: Big Swede
ENTRY.COMMENT: bit slow, tracked, 3-4wide into str, kept on

ENTRY.NAME: Majestic Wind
ENTRY.OWNER: Huston Racing Stable Ferraro Kyle and Stute Gary
ENTRY.COMMENT: pressed inside, steadied 1/2, saved ground, tired

ENTRY.NAME: dq-Kant Beat the Rock
ENTRY.COMMENT: stalked off rail, between, willingly, up for 2nd

ENTRY.NAME: Sunrise Journey
ENTRY.OWNER: Mia Familia Racing Stable and Ward Dudley
ENTRY.COMMENT: cleared, inside, came out past 1/8, held well

ENTRY.NAME: Established
ENTRY.COMMENT: brushed gate, chased outside rival, 3wide, evenly late, edged 2nd

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 3 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 83. Maiden Special Weight Purse 45000. FOR CALIFORNIA BRED OR CALIFORNIA SIRED MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: FLYMETOTHEMOONBABY cleared outer pair early, kicked away around the bend, entered the stretch two wide, remained well clear into the final furlong under right handed encouragement and was ridden out in the late stages. ISABEL LUDLOW chased off the rail early, went outside a rival around the bend, got bumped while four wide approaching the five-sixteenths pole, came five wide into the lane, kept on through the lane but was no match for the winner. THE MUSIC WE MAKE was closest in pursuit of the leader early, chased three wide into the turn, drifted out to bump ISABEL LUDLOW near the five-sixteenths pole, came four wide into the lane and weakened.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 4 6F Dirt CR: 87. Claiming Purse 24000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $12,500.

CLAIM.OWNER: Cunningham Stables and Huston Racing Stables

RACE.FOOTNOTES: A NEW PEACE trailed two wide into the turn, moved out around the bend then swung eight wide into the lane, rallied to the front in midstretch and kicked clear to win going away. CHOLLIMA tracked three wide into the turn, steered out six wide leaving the bend, launched a bid in upper stretch but got outkicked by the winner. DRIZELLA stumbled leaving the gate, moved up to chase two wide into the turn, shifted four wide into the lane, bid in upper stretch but was no match in the furlong grounds. FLAT OUT JOY broke a step slow from outside, went up to duel for command outside RAIN DIVA, battled around the turn and into the lane, fought to midstretch but weakened past the eighth pole. RAIN DIVA took control early then dueled inside FLAT OUT JOY for the lead, battled into the lane near the rail and gave way once overtaken.

ENTRY.OWNER: Alvarez Edwin G and Lopez Miguel
ENTRY.COMMENT: stumbled, inside-2wide, shifted 4wide into str, bid, faltered

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 5 5F Dirt CR: 95. Starter Allowance Purse 29000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $30,000 OR LESS. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since April 4 Allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MISTER BOLD chased from inside to the stretch, steered out in upper stretch, drew alongside the runner-up past the sixteenth pole and got up. SIGUR ROS cleared quickly, set all the pace on the inside into the lane, put to right handed urging in upper stretch, remained clear past the eighth pole, drifted late while challenged by MISTER BOLD and could not hold off the winner. MY SUMMER DREAM chased two wide, tipped out into the stretch, kept on for a clear third but could not threaten the winner. MOLTO VIVACE chased off the inside, three wide into the lane and weakened.

ENTRY.NAME: Mister Bold
ENTRY.COMMENT: chased inside, angled out, got up

ENTRY.NAME: My Summer Dream
ENTRY.COMMENT: chased 2wide, tipped out, kept on

ENTRY.NAME: Sigur Ros
ENTRY.COMMENT: sped clear, inside, drifted late, caught

ENTRY.NAME: Molto Vivace
ENTRY.COMMENT: chased off rail, 3wide into lane, weakened

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 6 5F Dirt CR: 86. Claiming Purse 23000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $12,500 (Maiden And Claiming Races For $10,000 Or Less Not Considered In Eligibility)(Any race at five furlongs or less not considered ).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: WEGONAHAVAGOODTIME raced up close between then was outkicked leaving the backstretch, took the turn two to three wide, got brushed by PERFECT D at the three-sixteenths pole, challenged from outside with a furlong remaining and proved best late. WHISKY MY GOD (ARG) vied three deep early, inched ahead outside a rival two wide on the turn, cleared past the quarter pole, challenged by the winner in the final furlong and yielded late. PERFECT D vied four the lead four then three deep early, chased four wide into the lane, drifted in and brushed the winner at the three-sixteenths pole while going up to challenge and faltered in the furlong grounds. RUN SNAPPY broke a step slow, raced outside a rival at the back four wide into the turn, moved into the three path then came back out a bit late on the turn, steered inward at the quarter pole and could not rally. EDINBURGH EXPRESS broke a step slow, chased two wide through the turn and failed to menace. MCWHERTER vied for the command inside rivals to the turn, pressured WHISKY MY GOD (ARG) around the bend, failed to keep up past the quarter pole and faded in the late stages. PER THE HORSE RACING INTEGRITY AND WELFARE UNIT, WEGONAHAVAGOODTIME HAS BEEN DQ'D FOR A POSITIVE TEST.

ENTRY.NAME: McWherter
ENTRY.COMMENT: vied inside, faded

ENTRY.COMMENT: chased 2-3wide, brushed 3/16, best late

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 7 5F Dirt CR: 81. Claiming Purse 14000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $6,250 (Maiden, Claiming, And Starter Races Not Considered In Eligibility)(Any Race at Five Furlongs or Less Not Considered).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: EQUIPO A broke through the gate and was reloaded, quickly cleared, showed the way three wide into the lane, roused in upper stretch, asked right handed midstretch then switched to the left hand in the final furlong and was ridden out to the wire. PERFECTO AMOR bobbled leaving the gate, chased between rivals, got a bit crowded early on the turn to lose some ground, spun three wide into the lane and showed a mild response to best the others. QUICK INTRO chased the winner inside a pair of rivals to the turn, saved ground through the bend and flattened to third. POLLO D'ORO broke out a bit at the start, chased three deep into the turn, four wide into the drive and weakened.

ENTRY.COMMENT: chased inside, flattened

ENTRY.COMMENT: bobbled, chased between, crowded 7/16, 3wide into str, gained 2nd

ENTRY.COMMENT: broke thru gate, cleared, 2-3wide, ridden out

ENTRY.NAME: Pollo d'Oro
ENTRY.COMMENT: broke out, chased 3deep, 4wide, weakened

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 8 6F Dirt CR: 94. Starter Allowance Purse 22000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $16,000 OR LESS. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since April 4 Allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MY DESTINY forwardly placed from outside early, chased outside a rival and shifted in to impede that foe entering the turn, took aim from outside four wide into the lane, took over past the quarter pole and cleared shortly after, met the bid from INDY'S STAR approaching the eighth pole and turned that rival away in a game victory. INDY'S STAR dropped back early, advanced around the bend while coming off the rail, launched a bid midstretch inside the winner but was turned away in the late stages. CLASSYMADEMOISELLE tracked just out of range, raced near the inside then drifted out around the bend, was no match for the top pair in the stretch run but finished a clear third. SWEET HEIDELBERG was prominent early inside rivals then chased the leader up the backstretch, got impeded by MY DESTINY entering the turn, drifted seven wide on the turn and weakened. APART OF MY CHARM vied outside rivals then cleared to take full control, led two then three wide around the bend, was overtaken past the quarter pole and gave way. THE REIGN SONG tracked well off the rail, got bothered by MY DESTINY near the half-mile pole, had to alter out when SWEET HEIDELBERG was impeded entering the turn, was carried eight wide into the stretch by that rival and had little left for the stretch run.

ENTRY.NAME: Indy's Star
ENTRY.COMMENT: dropped back, advanced inside-3wide turn, bid inside, turned away

ENTRY.NAME: Classymademoiselle
ENTRY.COMMENT: tracked, drifted turn, no match

ENTRY.NAME: Sweet Heidelberg
ENTRY.COMMENT: up close, impeded 7/16, drifted 7wide, weakened

ENTRY.NAME: My Destiny
ENTRY.COMMENT: forwardly placed, shifted in 7/16, aim 4wide, clear, held gamely

ENTRY.NAME: The Reign Song
ENTRY.OWNER: Halasz Thomas E and Lovingier Terry C
ENTRY.COMMENT: bothered 1/2, altered 7/16, carried wide

ENTRY.NAME: Apart of My Charm
ENTRY.COMMENT: cleared, led 2-3wide, gave way

RACE.RACE_TEXT: Great Lady M S. - Grade2 LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 9 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 97. Stakes Purse 200000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. By subscription of $100 each to accompany the nomination closed Thursday June 22, 2023 with 18 nominations, or by supplementary nomination of $4,000 due at time of entry. All horses shall pay $1,500 to pa ss entry box and $1,500 additional to start, with $200,000 guaranteed with $120,000 to the winner, $40,000 to second, $24,000 to third, $12,000 to fourth and $4,000 to fifth. Three Year Olds 119 lbs. Older 124 lbs. Non winners of a Graded Stake since Janu ary 24, 2021 allowed 3 lbs. Non winners of a Graded Stake since October 4, 2020 allowed 5 lbs. Starters to be named through the entry box by the closing time of entries. A trophy will be presented to the winning owner.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: EDA took control early setting the pace outside ELM DRIVE, dueled two then three wide while relinquishing the lead around the bend, battled into the final furlong, regained command with a sixteenth remaining and gamely prevailed. CHISMOSA tossed her head, bumped and lost path at the start, chased out of range outside a rival three wide into the turn, steered out around the bend and came six wide into the lane, closed in on the top pair from the middle portion of the track, drew alongside EDA in deep stretch but could not get by. ELM DRIVE pressed EDA from inside up the backstretch, moved up on even terms on the turn then inched ahead two wide leaving the bend, continued to hold a short advantage over EDA with a furlong left to run but got outkicked by the top pair in the final sixteenth. DANCE TO THE MUSIC brushed the gate, stalked four then three deep up the backstretch, came five wide into the stretch and lacked the needed response. AWAKE AT MIDNYTE stalked three deep then came in a bit to bump PAMMY'S READY near the half-mile pole, chased between foes two wide into the turn, entered the lane four wide and lacked a late bid. VEGAS MAGIC chased at the back outside a rival three wide into the turn, fell back to last and steered down to the rail around the bend then showed a mild response to improve position down the lane. PAMMY'S READY bumped leaving the gate, chased between foes then got bumped by outer rival and shuffled back early, raced near the inside on the turn then steered out four wide and failed to threaten. REAL FIRE took back when crowded between rivals shortly after the start, got put in tight between rivals at the half-mile pole, chased at the rear two wide into the turn, angled out and came six wide into the lane and had little left for the drive. ROSE MADDOX stalked the leading pair inside rivals to the turn, moved off the fence and chased three three wide into the lane and faded down the stretch.

ENTRY.NAME: Elm Drive
ENTRY.COMMENT: pressed, dueled inside-2wide, inched ahead, outkicked

ENTRY.NAME: Eda
ENTRY.COMMENT: set pressured pace outside, dueled outside, dug in, prevailed

ENTRY.COMMENT: stalked inside, 3wide into str, faded

ENTRY.COMMENT: tight early & 1/2, angled 6wide, empty

ENTRY.COMMENT: bumped start, shuffled early, 4wide into lane, no threat

ENTRY.NAME: Chismosa
ENTRY.COMMENT: tossed head/bumped/lost path, angled 6wide, rallied

ENTRY.NAME: Awake At Midnyte
ENTRY.COMMENT: stalked 3deep, between, 4wide into lane, no bid

ENTRY.NAME: Vegas Magic
ENTRY.OWNER: Aldabbagh Omar Cady Todd and Leatherman Ty
ENTRY.COMMENT: chased, 3-4wide, angled in turn, improved

ENTRY.NAME: Dance to the Music
ENTRY.OWNER: Red Baron's Barn LLC and Rancho Temescal LLC
ENTRY.COMMENT: brushed gate, stalked 4-3deep, 3-5wide, no bid
